# Blueprint Prompt Generator - Cursor Rules

## 1. Project Architecture

### 1.1 Directory Structure Principles
```
promptgen/
├── app/                    # Next.js 14 App Router
│   ├── layout.tsx          # Root layout with providers
│   ├── page.tsx            # Home/wizard entry
│   └── globals.css         # Tailwind + custom CSS variables
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # Shadcn/Radix primitives
│   ├── wizard/             # Wizard step components
│   └── selectable-card.tsx # Reusable interactive card
├── store/
│   └── useWizardStore.ts   # Zustand global state
├── utils/
│   ├── dictionary.ts       # Value-to-instruction mappings
│   └── markdown-generator.ts # Template literal engine
└── types/
    └── wizard.ts           # TypeScript interfaces
```

### 1.2 File Naming Conventions
| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `SelectableCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` prefix | `useWizardNavigation.ts` |
| Utils | camelCase | `markdownGenerator.ts` |
| Store | `use` prefix + Store suffix | `useWizardStore.ts` |
| Types | PascalCase | `WizardStep.ts` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `WIZARD_STEPS.ts` |

---

## 2. TypeScript Clean Code Standards

### 2.1 Type Definitions (STRICT MODE)
```typescript
// ✅ Required: Explicit return types for functions
function generateMarkdown(state: WizardState): string

// ✅ Required: Interface over type for extensibility
interface WizardState {
  currentStep: number;
  selections: WizardSelections;
}

// ✅ Required: Discriminated unions for step types
type StepType = 
  | { kind: 'single'; options: SingleChoiceOption[] }
  | { kind: 'multiple'; options: MultipleChoiceOption[] }

// ✅ Forbidden: Any type without explicit justification
// ❌ NO: const data: any
// ✅ YES: const data: unknown (with type guard)
```

### 2.2 Import Order
1. Next.js/React core imports
2. Third-party libraries (Zustand, Lucide)
3. Shadcn/Radix UI components
4. Custom components
5. Utils/Hooks/Store
6. Types

---

## 3. State Management Guidelines

### 3.1 Zustand Store Structure
```typescript
interface WizardStore {
  // Navigation
  currentStep: number;
  setCurrentStep: (step: number) => void;
  nextStep: () => void;
  prevStep: () => void;

  // Selections (Step 1-8)
  selections: WizardSelections;
  updateSelection: (step: keyof WizardSelections, value: any) => void;

  // Generation
  generatedPrompt: string;
  generatePrompt: () => void;
  resetWizard: () => void;
}
```

### 3.2 State Update Rules
- **Immutability First**: Never mutate state directly
- **Atomic Updates**: Use spread operators for partial updates
- **Type Safety**: All updates must preserve TypeScript types
- **No Side Effects in Store**: Pure state management only

---

## 4. Component Architecture

### 4.1 Selectable Card Contract
```typescript
interface SelectableCardProps {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  icon: LucideIcon;
  selected: boolean;
  onSelect: (id: string) => void;
  mode: 'single' | 'multiple';
  optionalText?: string;
  onOptionalTextChange?: (text: string) => void;
}
```

### 4.2 Component Hierarchy
```
WizardShell
├── Header
│   └── Stepper (1-8 indicators)
├── StepContent (dynamic based on currentStep)
│   ├── TypeStep
│   ├── IndustryStep
│   ├── AuthStep
│   ├── FeaturesStep
│   ├── DatabaseStep
│   ├── DesignStep
│   ├── DeployStep
│   └── AIStep
│       └── GenerateButton
└── Footer
    ├── BackButton
    └── NextButton
```

---

## 5. Markdown Generator Rules

### 5.1 Template Literal Structure
- Use tagged template literals for readability
- All selections MUST reference `utils/dictionary.ts`
- Include conditional rendering for optional fields
- Output must be valid Markdown

### 5.2 Dictionary Lookup Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
const designInstructions = dictionary.design.styles[selection.style];

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded values
const designInstructions = "Use rounded-2xl and soft shadows";
```

---

## 6. Performance Considerations

### 6.1 React Optimization
- Use `useCallback` for event handlers passed to child components
- Use `useMemo` for expensive computations (dictionary lookups)
- Lazy load step components with `dynamic()` import

### 6.2 Bundle Optimization
- Shadcn components: import only what's needed
- Lucide icons: tree-shakeable named imports
- No unused dependencies

---

## 7. Git & Commit Conventions

### 7.1 Branch Naming
- `feature/wizard-step-{N}`
- `fix/card-selection-bug`
- `docs/architecture-update`

### 7.2 Commit Messages
```
feat: add selectable card component
fix: resolve step navigation issue
docs: update architecture diagram
refactor: extract dictionary mappings
```
